 4 Steps to Franchising
 Read more







X






4 Steps to Franchising
 
There is an obligation for the Franchisee  to partner proactively in the process.  With our coaching they will be empowered to make decisions on: staff training, store design, site selection and equipment ordering.  Veyron carefully scrutinize all Franchisee applications to ensure that they can have a successful investment experience and the following process is observed:
 
1. Franchisee completes a Request for Consideration Form.
2. Phone interview with Veyron’s Development Director.
3. Franchisee submits Application Form.
4. Veyron supply Franchise Disclosure Document (FDD) for signature.

 









 SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY
 Read more







X






Corporate Social Responsibility
 
Eradicate Poverty
Veyron's core coporate social responsibility is the eradication of poverty in the world by focusing our efforts, sponsorships, and goals to enhace the lives of the less fortunate in one country at a time. We understand that there is an impact, directly/indirectly, on the communities that surround our businesses. Almost half the world — over 3 billion people — live on less than $2.50 a day. The GDP (Gross Domestic Product) of the 41 Heavily Indebted Poor Countries (567 million people) is less than the wealth of the world’s 7 richest people combined. The V Responsibility emphasized in our corporate culture starting with our employees, who make up our brand, are responsbile to support the poor labors, families, and children in our community by donating food, water, and other basic necessities. If you are organizing a fundraiser or special sponsorship program with the sole purpose to reduce poverty and help the less fortunate,Veyron is interested to hear about your special event.
 
Sustainability 
Veyron  recognize a responsibility of stewardship to protect our planet and its resources for future generations.   We foster sustainable practices by demonstrating thought leadership in the suppliers which we work with.

 









Meet The CEO
 Read more







X






Hayssam El-Masri
 
Mr. El Masri, President of Veyron Investment, an Investment holding company which nurtures & provides a high growth platform to North American retail brands in the GCC operating as one of the fastest growing retail market in the world such as Mr sub, Jugo Juice, and Van Houtte Cafe. 
 
During his 20+ year career path, Mr. El Masri has established himself as a well-respected and resourceful businessman, a highly successful investor and strategic financial advisor for mega real estate projects. He has created and re-structured numerous financial companies across the region, as well as successfully completed a number of acquisitions with total value of over SAR 10 billion. Mr. Hayssam El-Masri is one of the leading Advisory and Investment expert in the Gulf who has increased the activities within the investment ecosystem in the gulf. Mr. El-Masri is the Forbes Middle East Global Award Winner 2014 and he has appeared in major publications such as Arabia Business and Forbes Middle East
 
 

 



























